author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: AREA ROUNDUP: Honeoye boys soccer shuts out Midlakes
text: Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 2:01 AM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 2:01 AM Canandaigua, N.Y. CLIFTON SPRINGS — The Honeoye boys soccer team traveled to Midlakes High School and came away with a 2-0 win on Thursday. The two teams went into the second half tied 0-0. Colton Welch and Kyle Morsheimer each scored a goal for the Bulldogs, and the defense shut down the Screaming Eagles offense to earn the win. Honeoye is now 4-7-1 in the league, and Midlakes drops to 2-9 in the league. In other high school boys soccer action on Thursday: Naples 2, Bloomfield 1 OT Cole Rathbun assisted his brother Conrad two minutes into overtime to help the Big Green defeat the Bombers. Matt Barkley scored the first goal of the game for Naples (12-1-3) and then Trevor Hawkins tied the game for Bloomfield (10-5-1). Naples’ Jake Chapman and Bloomfield’s Bryce Beechler had eight saves each in goal. South Seneca 6, Marcus Whitman 0 Lincoln Bachman-Lowe scored two goals and Adam Wagner had four assists to lead the Falcons over the Wildcats. Skyler Rasmussen made six saves and recorded a shutout for South Seneca. GIRLS SOCCER Marcus Whitman 5, Romulus 0 Emily Thompson scored four goals to lead the Wildcats over the Warriors. Katrina Meyer and Ellie Nemitz combined in net for the shutout. GIRLS SWIMMING Victor 103, Fairport 83 Abby Fenn placed first in the 100 butterfly and the 200 free and was on the winning 200 medley relay team along with Mia Baggett, Natalie Zaravella and Caroline Wood. Zaravella won the 200 individual medley and 500 free and Baggett won the 100 breaststroke. GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Gananda 3, Sodus 0 The Blue Panthers swept the Spartans 25-6, 25-18 and 25-7. Gananda is now 12-0 in league. Alli Stark led the team with 10 assists. Canandaigua 3, Greece Athena 0 The Braves (4-8) swept Athena 25-18, 25-18 and 25-19. Outside hitter Sarah Braddon had seven kills and five aces and Libero Dale Sandle had 16 digs to lead Canandaigua. Sara Ciott had nine kills for the 6-11 Athena team. North Rose-Wolcott 3, Lyons 1 The Cougars were led by Abby Miraglia’s 21 assists and Kelly Crane’s 15 kills. Isis Tarver had 10 digs for the Lions. Penn Yan 3, Midlakes 0 The Mustangs (13-2) won 25-21, 26-24 and 25-15. Kelly Bray had 15 assists and six digs for Penn Yan, and Sydney Jones led Midlakes with 17 assists. By Messenger Post
